  "BR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCarter's numbers may be down somewhat this season, but he's still too good to ever consider benching. The veteran has a knack for finding the end zone, and should have a good game against rookie CB Will Allen and the Giants' secondary on Monday night. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1558\u0026key=12576\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRandy Moss\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIN - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMoss is listed as probable for Monday's game against the N.Y. Giants due to an ankle injury. He's been underachieving this season, but it's almost impossible to bench him based on his potential to post solid Fantasy numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1558\u0026key=133448\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Williams\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NO - Bass/Hull!",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Conwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble. With the lack of depth at tight end around the league, however, starting Conwell is something many Fantasy owners will have no choice but to do. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1558\u0026key=1456\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRichard Huntley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CAR - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHuntley will be the likely starter this weekend against San Francisco, but don't be surprised if he splits carries with Nick Goings. Avoid starting either back in Week 10 if at all possible. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1558\u0026key=12431\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Hayes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHayes ha!",
  "Date": "Sun, 18 Nov 2001 05:29:18 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c1093400.1075862414154.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Muhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1558\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best Fantasy quarterbacks in the league this season.   "=2762\u0026key=187528\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eReuben Droughns\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDroughns will likely split time with Lamont Warren in Detroit's backfield this weekend in James Stewart's absence.   "Brooks had a big game against San Francisco last weekend, throwing for 347 yards and two scores.   "HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, Weinke will be the starting quarterback for Sunday's game against San Francisco. However, he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133263\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDaunte Culpepper\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCulpepper is one pace for a good Fantasy season despite the lack of consistency in Minnesota's offense this season. He's one of the better quarterbacks in the league from a Fantasy perspective, and should be in your starting lineup on a weekly basis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c640753.1075862414251.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Michael Westbrook\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season, but he has caught three touchdown passes in his last four games. He'll face a Denver secondary this weekend that is vulnerable at best, so starting him in deeper leagues is worth considering. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been held in check in his last two games, catching only three passes for 38 yards.   "Mime-Version": "1.0",

  "d 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis has stepped up his play after beginning the season slowly. He's averaged 112 yards rushing over his last four games, and is once again emerging as a reliable Fantasy player. Give him the start in Week 10 against a Denver defense that is vulnerable to high scoring games. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBanks has played well of late, throwing five touchdowns in his last three games. He's got a good matchup this weekend against a Denver team that can be beaten through the air, but he's only worth considering in very deep Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762!",

  "e=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best Fantasy quarterbacks in the league this season. He'll face an Atlanta team on Sunday with a very vulnerable secondary, so be sure to start Favre this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=18738!",
  "ers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133448\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Williams\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NO - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWilliams is one of the better Fantasy backs in the league, and is a good player to use on a weekly basis. He'll face an Indianapolis defense that has been underachieving all season long, so Williams is a must-start.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133233\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAaron Brooks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NO - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/3/sffer1113ffr.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7",

  "Updated 10/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBecht had a huge game against St. Louis, posting five catches for 35 yards and two scores. He's been inconsistent this season, however, but his potential to post good numbers makes him worth starting at a position lacking quality players. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=798\u0026key=1265\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKeyshawn Johnson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJohnson caught 10 passes for 159 yards against Pittsburgh.   "Lockett, who suffered a rib injury last weekend against Denver, expects to play on Sunday against Philadelphia.   "Martin suffered a hamstring injury during Sunday's game against Dallas. He'll miss a few days of practice, but is expected to play in this weekend's game against Washington.   "BR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2125\u0026key=235122\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarvin Minnis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMinnis is unlikely to be available for Sunday's game against Seattle due to the sprained ankle he suffered during a Nov. 11 game against the Jets.   "Brunell's nagging leg injury might sideline him for Sunday's game against Baltimore. Jonathan Quinn has been preparing as if he will start the game, so right now you shouldn't count on Brunell this week as you set your lineups.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12753\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFred Taylor\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB JAC - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTaylor received a second medical opinion Tuesday that indicated his severe groin injury could keep him out up to three months and possibly the remainder of the season, according to the \u003cI\u003eFlorida Times-Union\u003c/I\u003e.   "Owens suffered a sprained left knee and ankle during the overtime session of last weekend's game against Carolina. The injuries aren't considered serious, however, and Owens is expected to be in the starting lineup on Sunday Indianapolis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2125\u0026start=31\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eTeams,\u0026nbsp;Rosters\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c!-- Pizzahut Presenting Logo Spotlight tag - Do not remove until 12-31-01 --\u003e",
  "Patriots Head Coach Bill Belichick announced late Monday that Brady will remain the starting quarterback for the remainder of the season, barring injury. This relegates Drew Bledsoe to a backup role and makes him useless from a Fantasy perspective. Brady might have his hands full passing against the Saints on Sunday, but he is a fairly safe weekly starter otherwise.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2125\u0026key=15\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Dolphins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT MIA - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDefensive tackle Daryl Gardener could miss the remainder of the season due to a fragmented disc in his back. He will miss at least one month to rest and rehabilitate the injury before being re-evaluated. Gardener's absence hurts the Dolphins' rush defense, which might be burned a little more by opposing running backs in the upcoming weeks.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT!",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 11/21/01",
  "T\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarring any setbacks, Banks will start Sunday's game against Philadelphia. Banks, who suffered a concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) is expected to return to practice on Wednesday at full strength.   "To": "tori.kuykendall@enron.com",
  "Wayne has a sprained knee ligament, and is doubtful for Sunday's game against New Orleans.   "Updated 10/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBruce hasn't been very consistent thus far, but he's far too talented to ever consider benching. Look for him to turn things around against the questionable N.Y. Jets secondary. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=892\u0026key=1366\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErnie Conwell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE STL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConwell has become a decent tight end from a Fantasy perspective this season. He's worth staring on a weekly basis if you don't have a more reliable tight end on your roster. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=892\u0026key=187503\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTrung Canidate\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB STL - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCanidate will !",
  "Westbrook has been less than mediocre this season, but he could have a decent outing against Carolina. He's had some success against the Panthers in the past, but he's still only worth starting in deeper leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=892\u0026key=1007\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eVinny Testaverde\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NYJ - Neal/McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTestaverde might not be a good start this week. The St. Louis defense can be opportunistic, and could very well make the Jets QB throw his first interception of the year.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=892\u0026key=1320\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWalter Rasby\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eRasby will likely get most of the work at tight end !",

  "Sanders left Sunday's game against San Diego after re-aggravating a hamstring injury. He was replaced by MarTay Jenkins, and did not return to the game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1196\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEric Moulds\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BUF - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMoulds finally emerged from an extended slump, catching six passes for 196 yards and two TDs against Miami. He also lost a fumble, and Fantasy owners should still remember that Moulds has been a disappointment for most of the year. Don't be surprised if he follows his best outing of the year with a mediocre performance.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1011\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAlex Van Pelt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BUF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE!",

  "day's game against Atlanta due to a shoulder injury. His status for next weekend's game against New Orleans is unknown at this time. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1191\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDerrick Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander caught two passes for 56 yards in his return from a rib injury. He was not open often, and Alexander may continue to be a Fantasy disappointment if he stays healthy.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1004\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Chandler\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB ATL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "e of his inconsistency. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1514\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eQadry Ismail\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe Jaguars held Ismail to three catches for 44 yards. Despite his quiet statistical performance, Ismail remains a must-start player for any Fantasy team. He is one of the most complete and underrated receivers in the AFC.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=192266\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJason Brookins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrookins rushed for 82 yards and two TDs at Jacksonville, but also lost a fumble. The rookie RB is talented, but too erratic to be a Fantasy starter on most teams right now.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1120t.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7",
  "nsistent to be a starter on better Fantasy teams as the playoffs approach. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner caught four passes for only 33 yards on Sunday. The rookie has slowed down considerably in the past few weeks, and now seems like a risk during the Fantasy homestretch. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1089\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKi-Jana Carter\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "od outing against New England, catching five catches for 78 yards and a touchdown. He may not be the most dependable Fantasy receiver, but he is worth starting in deeper leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1511\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJoe Horn\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NO - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHorn had another solid outing, catching four passes for 97 yards against New England. He?s been a very dependable receiver in recent weeks and is worth starting on a weekly basis.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB OAK - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "om=734\u0026key=235249\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLaDainian Tomlinson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SD - Hunter \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTomlinson was held out of the end zone, but he had a good day against Arizona nonetheless. The rookie tailback had 145 scrimmage yards, including 13 receptions, in San Diego?s 20-17 loss. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=12375\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDoug Flutie\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SD - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFlutie had a solid game, throwing for 308 yards and two touchdowns against Arizona. However, he?s only worth starting when the matchup is to his advantage. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=734\u0026key=1003\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJake Plummer\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB ARI - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c!",

  "Coach Brian Billick expects Grbac to be ready for Sunday's game against Jacksonville, but the quarterback wasn't so sure. \"I'm day-to-day.   "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 10/23/01",
  "Taylor has been ruled out of Sunday's game against Baltimore and his status for next week's game remains uncertain. \"All I know is that, from week to week, they increase his exercises and change of direction,\" head coach Tom Coughlin told \u003ci\u003eThe Florida Times-Union\u003c/i\u003e. \"It remains to be seen when Fred will be able to play. Progress is slow. I'm hoping he responds well this week, then we can make some kind of legitimate guess [about a return date] next week.\" Taylor has been inactive since severely injuring his groin on Sept 23.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1886\u0026key=187617\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDennis Northcutt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eNorthcutt left Sunday's game because of a concussion.   "The Chicago Sun-Times\u003c/I\u003e is now reporting that Dez White will start in place of Robinson, with Terrell being used as the team's third receiver. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1886\u0026key=1282\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Martin\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ATL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMartin will have an X-ray on his broken right collarbone this week.   "To": "tori.kuykendall@enron.com",
  "Todd Heap\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHeap did not play Sunday but head coach Brian Billick told \u003ci\u003eThe Baltimore Sun\u003c/i\u003e he is optimistic that the rookie will play in this week's game. Monitor Green's progress during the week before deciding whether to use him in Week !",

  "Dixon missed Monday night's 10-9 loss to the Philadelphia Eagles due to a sprained ankle.   "Dyson is recovering from a thumb injury but is expected to play in Monday's game against the Steelers. He is expected to participate in practice.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=486\u0026key=1174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEddie George\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGeorge suffered a thumb injury in Sunday's game.   "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 10/24/01",
  "Taylor has been ruled out of Sunday's game against Baltimore and his status for next week's game remains uncertain. \"All I know is that, from week to week, they increase his exercises and change of direction,\" head coach Tom Coughlin told \u003ci\u003eThe Florida Times-Union\u003c/i\u003e. \"It remains to be seen when Fred will be able to play. I'm hoping he responds well this week, then we can make some kind of legitimate guess [about a return date] next week.\" Taylor has been inactive since severely injuring his groin on Sept 23.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=486\u0026key=187617\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDennis Northcutt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eNorthcutt left Sunday's game because of a concussion.   "To": "tori.kuykendall@enron.com",

  "McNabb passed for just 133 yards and no touchdowns Sunday against Oakland, but he didn't get intercepted either.   "Sunday's game against Arizona. These numbers aren't great for the Fantasy owner, and they came against a weak Cardinals' secondary.   "Updated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePrice caught eight passes for 151 yards and a TD at San Diego. While Price is still inconsistent, he appears to have improved enough to start for Fantasy teams occasionally.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHasselbeck had his best game as a pro, throwing for 230 yards, two TDs and no interceptions. But he continued to have some troubles completing key passes and getting the ball downfield on important downs.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=187382\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eShaun Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica!",
  "X-FileName": "TKUYKEN (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\TKUYKEN (Non-Privileged)\\Kuykendall, Tori\\Deleted Items",
  "X-From": "Commissioner.COM \u003cnoreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com\u003e",
  "X-Origin": "Kuykendall-T",
  "X-To": "Kuykendall, Tori \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=TKUYKEN\u003e",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": "",
  "at Philadelphia. This outing could put him firmly in place as the Raiders' featured back while Tyrone Wheatley remains sidelined.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon passed for just 158 yards, no touchdowns and no interceptions in Sunday's game at Philadelphia. He was facing a tall challenge in the Eagles' secondary, and we expect he will rebound with better stats in future weeks.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=133361\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonovan McNabb\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB PHI - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "but the Broncos let Olandis Gary carry the ball 10 times for 37 yards also. Denver appears to have lost some confidence in Anderson this year.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1790\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Patten\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePatten caught five passes for 62 yards and a TD at Denver. He should continue to be a scoring threat as long as he remains one of New England's top two receivers.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1253\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTroy Brown\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1023t.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "s overcame a sprained ankle to play against the Bills, and caught two passes for five yards. One of his catches was good for a one-yard TD, and Jones may now get much of his numbers on short TD catches. Doug Flutie seems to prefer his wideouts over the tight end when the Chargers are outside the red zone.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1072\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLarry Centers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BUF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCenters was limited to eight receiving yards on four catches by San Diego. The Bills ideally want to get the ball downfield to their wideouts and Jay Riemersma, so don't expect good numbers from Centers ecery week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=133393\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003ePeerless Price\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BUF - Free A!",
  "t the opposition is.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1440\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eStephen Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB WAS - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis rushed for 107 yards against the Giants, but was held out of the end zone again. He is still running for good yardage, but the Redskins continue to score via the pass when they are able to move the ball.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3664\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBanks threw for 190 yards, two TDs and was not intercepted by the Giants. Right, now the erratic QB is playing well enough to be used as a Fantasy reserve.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e"
}

  "\u003chtml\u003e\u003cdiv style='background-color": "'\u003e\u003cDIV\u003eHello Mrs. Kuykendall, hope all is well with you and the baby.\u0026nbsp; All done with my trip round the world (and got a big boy email account as well now that employers will be looking at it!) and of course i have to go through the dreaded interviewing process to find gainful employment..... just spoke with a head hunter lady who is going to help me find a trading job in gas/power and of course i left her your name as one of my many pristine references.\u0026nbsp; I left keith's as well.\u0026nbsp; Hopefully you two are both big swingin' dicks in the industry these days and my potential new employers will swoon over your glowing praise!\u0026nbsp; For now though i am trapped at my parents' house wasting days doing little other than reading.\u0026nbsp; Its indian summer here in mass today though so i'm going to get outside before the sun goes down.\u0026nbsp; Read a couple of good books while i was away, Rich Man Poor Man by Irwin Shaw and Memoirs of a Geisha w!",

Expect fine numbers from him the rest of the way.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year. He will be a key player on many title teams, and should never be benched. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Graham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday. If Graham doesn't play, Trevor Gaylor will start in his place and Nate Turner will be signed off the practice squad. The Chargers are already missing their No. 3 receiver, Tim Dwight, due to complications of a collapsed lung. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NE - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith rushed for a career-high 156 yards and a touchdown Saturday. He has been one of the best runners in the AFC and will help carry your team to Fantasy glory.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday. He hurt himself on a PAT attempt, but Gramatica is expected to play on December 29.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game. He should be able to start against the Jaguars, but he may play with some pain in his thumb. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1264\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Graham\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SD - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c16782137.1075855445187.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Richardson hasn't been a consistent scoring threat this year.   "Gadsden (hamstring) might miss his second consecutive game this week.   "Graham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday.   "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday.   "Hicks is expected to miss this week's game with a hamstring injury, and may miss the rest of the season. Eddie George should assume a regular workload once again. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3696\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith is day to day with a hip injury.   "Gramatica sat out practice Wednesday, but is expected to test his injured leg on Thursday. Doug Brien and Brad Daluiso worked out Wednesday for the Buccaneers, who might sign one if Martin Gramatica can't kick against the Baltimore Ravens this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3837\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTrent Dilfer will start this week in place of Hasselbeck, whose separated left shoulder is too sore for him to play.    Coach Mike Holmgren said Wednesday that Hasselbeck aggravated the injury, which he's had since the third week of the season, against the New York Giants last Sunday.   \"There's a chance I might have him and he could play in an emergency-type situation, but he's pretty sore,\" Holmgren said.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "McCardell is listed as probable with a thigh injury. He should be able to start this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3837\u0026key=235203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Chambers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChambers is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced on Wednesday and should be able to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1288\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames McKnight\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcKnight is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced and is hopeful of playing this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "Updated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHenry will sit out again this week with a sprained knee. Shawn Bryson will start for the second consecutive week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair missed practice Wednesday because of back pain.   \"I'm going to try to do some things tomorrow and hope it loosens up and not have as much pain as I had today,\" McNair said.   \"I'm not going to go out and try to force the issue. If it's still sore and still tight where I can't have all my mechanics right, I'm not going to force the issue.\"     The Titans listed him as questionable yet again Wednesday, but McNair likely will play \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Warrick, who was benched late in last week's game, is expected to start. He has been a disappointment this year and Fantasy players should not use him at this point of the postseason.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman (thumb) may attempt to practice late in the week.   "Bettis, sidelined by a groin injury, returned to the practice field Thursday for the first time in a month. \"Still questionable,\" coach Bill Cowher said. \"He did more today. We'll see how he feels (Friday) and go from there. We'll take it day to day.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1393\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDoug Brien\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrien signed a one-year contract Thursday night with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, who will use him against Baltimore if Martin Gramatica can't kick this week. Gramatica strained his right hamstring during a 48-21 victory over the Saints last week. Coach Tony Dungy hasn't ruled him out for Saturday night's game against Baltimore, however the club wanted to have a backup plan in case the Pro Bowl kicker isn't ready. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Bouman took a few snaps Thursday but didn't appear to meet coach Dennis Green's \"full strength\" criteria for starting against Green Bay.   Spergon Wynn is likely to start Sunday, though coaches didn't discuss the issue after Thursday's practice. Bouman didn't participate in the team's morning walk-through, when players work on plays without fully suiting up. And during the portion of the regular practice that reporters were allowed to watch, Wynn took more snaps than Bouman. A trainer said Wynn continued to take more snaps later in the closed portion of practice.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1152\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJerome Bettis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "CB Shawn Springs, who was suspended for the past four games, will not start on Sunday against San Diego. He may play a reserve role, however, but his playing time will likely be limited. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman will miss Sunday's game against Green Bay due to a thumb injury.   "Emanuel (knee) is expected to play on Sunday against Chicago.   "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Gadsden has been practicing this week and may be able to play. But his hamstring injury may limit his productivity. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair was limited in practice on Thursday. He is still expected to play. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "McNair was excused from practice on Friday due to a family illness.   "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1228c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",

  "To": "tori.kuykendall@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFinneran is listed as probable with a knee injury. He is expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1499\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis has been elevated to the No. 2 tight end slot over rookie David Martin. He will see a considerable amount of playing time now that he is healthy, because Green Bay employs many double tight end sets in the red zone. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Wynn will start Sunday's game against the Green Bay Packers in place of the injured Todd Bouman. Wynn, who played in most of last week's loss to Jacksonville, is far too inexperienced to start this deep into the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=136\u0026key=1041\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDrew Bledsoe\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, the Chicago Bears are interested in acquiring Bledsoe. With Tom Brady seemingly entrenched as New England's quarterback, it seems that Bledsoe has become expendable to the Patriots.   "Barber suffered a slightly sprained ankle during Sunday's game against Philadelphia. He was removed from the game for precautionary measures, and is expected to start in Week 17 against Arizona. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=235031\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eCorrell Buckhalter\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/31/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Buckhalter suffered an ankle injury during Sunday's 24-21 win over the N.Y. Giants. The rookie tailback is listed as day to day.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=235123\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTravis Minor\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB MIA - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/31/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMinor got most of the carries during Sunday's 21-14 win over Atlanta. The rookie compiled 98 all-purpose yards and a touchdown in the game, and may have overtaken Lamar Smith as Miami's featured back. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/31/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Byrd suffered a concussion and a leg bruise during Sunday's 30-7 loss to Arizona.   "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Tue, 1 Jan 2002 08:54:00 -0800 (PST)",
  "Foster (thigh) is expected to play in Sunday's game against Chicago. However, he is far too risky to start at this point in the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=1186\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBert Emanuel\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eEmanuel (knee) is expected to play on Sunday against Chicago. However, he's too risky to start at this point in the Fantasy Football season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad (turf toe) will not play this week, and may miss the rest of the season. Isaac Byrd will likely start in his place again. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Gramatica missed Saturday's game against Baltimore due to a leg injury. He will attempt to practice on Wednesday, but early indications seem to point to Doug Brien handling the kicking duties in Week 17.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=1096\u0026key=1372\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFrank Wycheck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE TEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/31/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWycheck left Sunday's game against Cleveland in the first quarter due to a thigh bruise.   "Kelly suffered a shoulder injury during Sunday's 21-14 loss to the Miami Dolphins.   "\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=4\u003eLatest NFL Player News\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=78977.7\u0026random=641\u0026key=1264\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Graham\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SD - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGraham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday.   "Bryson will start in place of the injured Travis Henry this week.   "Bouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game.   "Bouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game.   "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Garcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib.   "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Minnis hasn't done much to help Fantasy owners this year.
